18 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 27A O.S. 2021, Section 2-11-401.1,
19 is amended to read as follows:
20 Section 2-11-401.1. As used in the Oklahoma Used Tire Recycling
21 Act:
22 1. "ASTM" means the American Society for Testing and Materials;
23 2. "Automobile" means every motor vehicle of the type
24 constructed and used for the transportation of ten (10) persons or
Req. No. 17204 Page 1

1 less , including the driver, or used for the transportation of
2 property. Provided, however, that the automobile's gross vehicle
3 weight rating does not exceed sixteen thousand (16,000) pounds;
4 3. "Automotive dismantler and parts recycler" means the same as
5 defined in Section 591.2 of Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
6 4. "Commission" means the Oklahoma Tax Commission;
7 5. "Department" means the Department of Environmental Quality;
8 6. "End use" means a Department-approved ultimate economic use
9 for a used tire or tire-derived product, including granulated
10 rubber, ground rubber, tire chips, tire-derived aggregate, tire-
11 derived fuel and tire shreds;
12 7. "Fund" means the Used Tire Recycling Indemnity Fund;
13 8. "Granulated rubber" means particulate rubber composed of
14 mainly nonspherical particles that span a broad range of maximum
15 particle dimensions, from below four hundred twenty-five thousandths
16 (0.425) of a millimeter (40 mesh) to twelve (12) millimeters (0.47
17 inches) pursuant to current ASTM standards;
18 9. "Ground rubber" means particulate rubber composed of mainly
19 nonspherical particles that span a broad range of maximum particle
20 dimensions, from below four hundred twenty-five thousandths (0.425)
21 of a millimeter (40 mesh) to two (2) millimeters (0.08 inches)
22 pursuant to current ASTM standards;
23 10. "Motorcycle" means a motor vehicle of a type defined in
24 Section 1-135 of Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
Req. No. 17204 Page 2

1 11. "Motor-driven cycle" means a motor vehicle of a type
2 defined in Section 1-136 of Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
3 12. "Motor vehicle" means the same as defined in Section 1-134
4 of Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
5 13. "Priority cleanup list" means a list, created and
6 maintained by the Department, of:
7 a. unpermitted dumps which did not exist when the owner
8 took possession of the property where the tires are
9 located, and were created without the consent of or
10 benefit to the owner of the property, and
11 b. such other tire dumps designated by the Department
12 pursuant to Section 2-11-401.6 of this title;
13 14. "Reusable tire" means a tire that has been previously used
14 on a vehicle, not currently mounted on a vehicle, but can be legally
15 placed into service for vehicle use in Oklahoma;
16 15. "Semitrailer" means the same as defined in Section 1-162 of
17 Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
18 16. "Tire" means any solid or air-filled covering for vehicle
19 wheels;
20 17. "Tire chips" means pieces of scrap tires that have a basic
21 geometrical shape and are generally between twelve (12) millimeters
22 (0.47 inches) and fifty (50) millimeters (1.97 inches) in size and
23 have most of the wire removed pursuant to current ASTM standards;
24
Req. No. 17204 Page 3

1 18. "Tire dealer" means any person engaged in the business of
2 selling new and used tires to final consumers, not for resale;
3 19. "Tire-derived aggregate" means pieces of scrap tires that
4 have a basic geometrical shape and are generally between twelve (12)
5 millimeters (0.47 inches) and three hundred five (305) millimeters
6 (12.01 inches) in size and are intended for use in civil engineering
7 applications pursuant to ASTM standards;
8 20. "Tire-derived fuel" means whole tires or processed tires
9 that can be used for energy or fuel recovery pursuant to current
10 ASTM standards;
11 21. "Tire-derived fuel facility" or "TDF facility" means a
12 facility that uses processed tires or whole used tires for energy or
13 fuel recovery;
14 22. "Tire-derived product" means matter that:
15 a. is derived from a process that uses whole tires as a
16 feedstock, including chipping for the purpose of fuel
17 recovery, granulating and grinding,
18 b. adheres to established engineering or other
19 appropriate specifications or to established product
20 end-user specifications or customer conditions of
21 acceptance,
22 c. has a demonstrated benefit associated with the end
23 use, and
24
Req. No. 17204 Page 4

1 d. can be used as a substitute for or in conjunction with
2 a commercial product or raw material;
3 23. "Tire shreds" means pieces of scrap tires that have a basic
4 geometrical shape and are generally between fifty (50) millimeters
5 (1.97 inches) and three hundred five (305) millimeters (12.01
6 inches) in size pursuant to current ASTM standards;
7 24. "Trailer" means the same as defined in Section 1-180 of
8 Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
9 25. "Used tire" means an unprocessed whole tire or tire part
10 that can no longer be used for its originally intended purpose but
11 can be beneficially reused as approved by the Department. Any used
12 tire collected in accordance with the requirements of the Oklahoma
13 Used Tire Recycling Act is not considered to be discarded. A tire
14 that can be used, reused or legally modified to be reused for its
15 original intended purpose shall not be a used tire;
16 26. "Used tire processing" means altering the form of whole
17 used tires by shredding, chipping or other method approved by the
18 Department, except baling and pyrolysis. For purposes of this act
19 only, tire pyrolysis shall, for a five-year period ending on July 1,
20 2031, meet the definition of used tire processing until July 1,
21 2031, but not thereafter. Any tire pyrolysis facility shall not be
22 considered an advanced recycling facility but rather a used tire
23 recycling facility and subject to all applicable statutes and rules
24 for such facilities;
Req. No. 17204 Page 5

1 27. "Used tire recycling facility" means any place which is
2 permitted as a solid waste disposal site, in accordance with the
3 Oklahoma Solid Waste Management Act, at which used tires are
4 processed; and
5 28. "Vehicle" means the same as defined in Section 1-186 of
6 Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
