8 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 27A O.S. 2021, Section 2-11-401.4,
9 is amended to read as follows:
10 Section 2-11-401.4. A. Compensation to used tire facilities
11 and tire-derived fuel or TDF facilities pursuant to this section
12 shall be limited to facilities located in Oklahoma. Compensation
13 for used tire activities pursuant to this section shall be limited
14 to used tires from Oklahoma. A used tire recycling facility or
15 tire-derived fuel or TDF facility may transport and deliver used
16 tires collected from Oklahoma to an out-of-state used tire recycling
17 facility or TDF facility but shall not be eligible for compensation
18 from the Used Tire Recycling Indemnity Fund for those used tires.
19 To be eligible, applicants for compensation shall be in compliance
20 with the Oklahoma Used Tire Recycling Act.
21 B. The monies accruing annually to the Used Tire Recycling
22 Indemnity Fund shall be allocated first to the Department of
23 Environmental Quality Revolving Fund, to be used for implementing
24 applicable requirements related to the control of mobile and area
Req. No. 17204 Page 12

1 sour ces of air emissions, for monitoring and modeling the impacts on
2 Oklahoma of air pollution from other states, for implementing and
3 enforcing other applicable air pollution control requirements or for
4 other environmental programs or projects. The amount of money
5 allocated for this purpose shall be twenty-four and one-tenth
6 percent (24.1%) of the funds produced by the two-dollar-and-ninety-
7 cent per tire fee assessed pursuant to division (1) of subparagraph
8 a of paragraph 1 of subsection A of Section 2-11-401.2 of this title
9 and subparagraph b of paragraph 1 of subsection A of Section 2-11-
10 401.2 of this title; provided, in no event shall the amount
11 allocated annually exceed the 3-year average of the total fiscal
12 year amounts allocated in fiscal years 2015, 2016 and 2017 and any
13 amount in excess of the 3-year average shall be placed to the credit
14 of the General Revenue Fund. After this allocation is deducted, the
15 balance of the monies shall be allocated as follows:
16 1. Two and one-fourth percent (2.25%), not to exceed Twenty
17 Thousand Dollars ($20,000.00) per month, to the Oklahoma Tax
18 Commission and five and three-fourths percent (5.75%), not to exceed
